title: Carroll, Homestead win, gain playoff match, Dwenger, Leo, Woodlan pass first postseason tests;playoff week #1
text:
Carroll, Homestead win, gain playoff match, Dwenger, Leo, Woodlan pass first postseason tests;playoff week #1 
By Dean Pantazi -21Alive October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 12:09 AM EDT 
UNDATED (21Alive) - Carroll and Homestead will meet each other a second time, this time in the playoffs, after the two were among the winners Friday night in Week 1 of the high school football postseason. 
The Chargers won their 6A battle with Warsaw 49-21 as Aidan Smith threw for two touchdowns and ran for a third, while Blake Schumacher returned an interception for a touchdown and Jack Givens took an blocke punt in for another tally.

Andrew Jensen threw two touchdown passes for Warsaw. 
Drew Keszei passed for 234 yards and four touchdwns and ran for 11 yarda and another score in leading Homestead's 48-14 win over Northrop, and Carroll will play at Homestead in the 6A sectional final. 
in 4A, Amaun Clark and Peter Winklejohn each ran for two touchdowns as third ranked Dwenger ended Wayne's season with a 42-6 win, and Dwenger will play at New Haven next. 
Leo also advanced by trouncing Logansport 56-19 and the Lions play South Side in the second round. 
In 3A Luers set a school record for points in a game with their 82-52 win over Northwestern, and the combined total of 134 points was a state playoff record. 
Miitchell VanBrocklin ran for 156 yards and scored three times as fourth ranked Woodlan remained unbeaten with their 35-7 win at Central Noble.
